$ VBA - language: keyword optional

→ development/languages/VBA/objects/err[Optional parameters] allow to define default values for sub/function parameters that need not be specified when the sub/function is called.

gh|about-VBA|/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters/keyword-optional.bas|one-to-one|

For truly optional parameters (that is: optional parameters without specifying a default value), → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters/keyword-isMissing[`isMissing()`]
can be used to check if an actual value was passed for the argument.

